## 7.3 Image–Text Alignment Results

CLIP (Contrastive Language–Image Pretraining) cosine similarity is applied to assess how well generated images match the generated text (summaries/prompts). All three Stable Diffusion variants were evaluated as shown in Table 12.

**Table 12: Image–Text Evaluation Across SD Variants**

| Model | Backbone | Cosine Similarity ↑ | Contrast Ratio ↑ | Key Features |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| SD-1.5 Baseline | SD-1.5 | 0.280 | 1.290 | Simple prompts, no re-ranking |
| SD-2.1 Enhanced | SD-2.1 | 0.274 | 1.265 | Metadata prompts + k6 re-ranking |
| SD-2.1 Optimized | SD-2.1 | 0.230 | 1.606 | Metadata + k8 expansion |
| SD-Turbo | SD-Turbo | 0.278 | 1.318 | Fastest; metadata-aware prompting |

SD-1.5 and SD-Turbo perform similarly in semantic alignment with text. SD-2.1 Optimized trades accuracy for diversity and contrast. SD-Turbo is significantly faster with minimal CLIP degradation.

