## 7.5 Qualitative Image Comparisons

A side-by-side visual evaluation further demonstrates the difference among the models as shown in Table 14. When comparing news headline images, SD-Turbo generated a wide variety of vivid imagery while SD-1.5 relied on a more conservative and realistic depiction. Ground-truth images allow researchers to determine if there are any inconsistencies between an image's objects, background, or general context. They provide a reference point against which all generated images can be compared to ensure that they are accurate, relevant, and contextualized within the news article being reported.

The example above is an article regarding the state of Rajasthan's government plan to deploy 400 outdoor patient department (OPD) vans. This was done to help treat patients who have non-COVID related diseases while COVID-19 continues to ravage the country. Within this article, the following points have been highlighted: enhanced access to improved public health care; mobile units to treat patients; and, a government program to reduce the amount of time patients are waiting for treatment.

This statistical data corresponds to the increased CLIP similarity score (0.35) between SD-Turbo's generated images and the news article description.

